Jeff-

Sorry about your troubles.  It makes me think I dodged a bullet -- I'm
getting the folks who painted my bus to install the windows.  It was the
window installation that closed the deal.  My rationale was that if any
paint gets scratched during the installation, it was the paint guy(s) who
did it, and who better to fix the paint?  Also, I'm learning to pick my
battles.  It'll be nice having it done for me.  (I will have to do the
driver & passenger roll-up windows, though.  I hope those aren't too hard.)

Now I've got to start thinking about installing the motor.  Yes, I'll be
doing that myself -- never performed such a task before -- there has to be
a first time...

-David

P.S.  I have to remember that confidence is what you feel before you
understand the problem!


